I don’t know — the excerpts you provided do not contain a complete, parcel‑specific permit application checklist for constructing a small multi‑family building in UN3. I can only pull from the limited “application materials” text in the retrieved context. Below are the items explicitly listed in the provided zoning excerpts; you will need the City’s full permit application checklist and the parcel’s built‑form overlay (Chapter 540) to get a complete, site‑specific list.

Items explicitly required in the provided zoning excerpts (from “Application materials”):
- A detailed project description. (Context 4)  
- Scaled maps and plans, dimensional renderings, and other materials that identify and describe: (Context 4)
  - Primary conservation areas;  
  - Public river corridor views;  
  - Buildable area;  
  - Existing and proposed topography and drainage patterns;  
  - Proposed storm water and erosion and sediment control practices;  
  - Existing and proposed vegetation to be removed and established;  
  - Ordinary high water level, blufflines, and all required setbacks;  
  - Existing and proposed structures;  
  - Existing and proposed impervious surfaces; and  
  - Existing and proposed subsurface sewage treatment systems.  

Why this is incomplete / what I need to give a full checklist:
- The retrieved context does not include the Built Form Overlay (Chapter 540) development standards (setbacks, heights, frontage, lot‑area/width rules, FAR, etc.) that are essential to a UN3 permit application. (See Contexts 1–3 for references to overlays.)  
- The excerpts do not provide the city’s full permit application/plan set requirements (site plan, surveys, legal description, ownership proof, construction drawings, structural calculations, fire and life‑safety plans, mechanical/plumbing/electrical, erosion control permit details, parking calculations, landscape plan, fees, contractor licensing, etc.).

If you want a complete, site‑specific permit checklist I can provide it if you either (a) give the parcel’s built‑form overlay designation (or the parcel/zoning lookup), or (b) allow me to consult the City of Minneapolis permit/application guidance and Chapter 540.
